    Reference

    All functions

    axes_identify()

    axes_identify Identifies plot axes location

    color_cluster()

    color_cluster groups pixels of each curve in the image based on color using k-medoids clustering

    fig_clean()

    fig_clean Removes color values close to white, also possible to remove text on plot, useful for gridlines on KM curves

    fig_summarize()

    Figure Summarization

    img_read()

    img_read loads a jpeg or jpg or PNG file and turns into into arrays for further processing.

    impute_overlap()

    Impute Overlapping Values

    lines_isolate()

    lines_isolate Select the final singular y values for each curve (Note: this is where additional event detection could be performed)

    overlap_detect()

    overlap_detect detects potential overlap between curves and "fills in the gaps" using knn similarity

    range_detect()

    range_detect detects how X and y pixel values map to time and survival values respectively

    survival_digitize()

    Survival Digitization
